-- World Bank Nominee Kim to Travel to Brazil, India, China, Japan
-- B y   I a n   K a t z
-- 2012-03-26T20:32:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/world-bank-nominee-kim-to-travel-to-brazil-india-china-japan.html
Jim Yong Kim, the U.S. nominee to
head the  World Bank , will travel to  Asia ,  Africa  and  Latin
America  to solicit ideas for the institution, the U.S. Treasury
Department said in a statement today.  The trip will begin tomorrow and run through April 9, the
Treasury said. He will travel to  China ,  Japan ,  Brazil ,  Mexico ,
 Ethiopia  and  India .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Wellisz in Washington at 
 cwellisz@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
